name: Melodious Warbler
rangeDescription: Southwestern palearctic; winters in savanna of western africa
description: Medium-sized warbler, light olive-brown above and yellowish below with a rather long bill. Compared to Icterine Warbler, wings are shorter and lack the pale panel.

name: Rivoli's Hummingbird
rangeDescription: Mountains of southern arizona, new mexico, and texas to northeastern nicaragua
description: Very large for a hummingbird; size alone separates from many other species. Males are green overall with darker blackish chest and belly.

name: White-bellied Pygmy-Tyrant
rangeDescription: East slope of andes of peru (huánuco) to western bolivia (santa cruz)
description: A tiny puffball of feathers that looks like a bumblebee crossed with a down pillow. Minute size and compact shape prevent confusion with most other species, but also note the faint dusky streaking on whitish underparts, indistinct black crescent behind the eye, and olive-yellow upperparts.

name: Four-banded Sandgrouse
rangeDescription: Savanna and thornscrub of sub-saharan africa
description: A small, short-tailed, intricately marked sandgrouse. The distinctive male has black marks on top of the head and three bands across the underparts.

name: Minas Gerais Tyrannulet
rangeDescription: South-central bahia to central minas gerais, in eastern brazil
description: Small flycatcher with a long tail. Olive-green above, yellowish below, with two yellow wingbars.
